title: Hanne Gråhns
text:
Hanne Gråhns (born 29 August 1992) is a Swedish former <a href="Association%20football">football</a> midfielder who played for <a href="KIF%20%C3%96rebro%20DFF">KIF Örebro DFF</a>.
At the <a href="Football%20at%20the%202016%20Summer%20Olympics%20%E2%80%93%20Women%27s%20tournament">2016 Summer Olympics</a> Gråhns was an <a href="Substitute%20%28association%20football%29">alternate</a> for the <a href="Sweden%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Sweden national team</a>, who came second in the tournament.
When Örebro suffered a shock <a href="Promotion%20and%20relegation">relegation</a> from the Damallsvenskan in 2017, Gråhns remained loyal to the club. She retired from football after captaining the team to promotion in 2018.
